<p>French pronunciation of some common English word comes in with rather funny effect.  "This" is always "Zeese" &amp; the is "Ze".  She is pessimistic &amp; thinks the war cannot possibly end for four years or more unless we loose.  She seems to believe in the fact of England reclaiming Belgium, but <strike>thought</strike> thinks we have underrated the job.<br/>Nearly every night lately the Boche has come over with his bombs, but none have been dropped very near the camp.  It provides a little excitement for a time, but one speedily gets used to them for the danger is not very great.</p>
